 ┌───────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │         File          │                Purpose                 │
  ├───────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ wifi-watchdog.sh      │ Generic — deploy identically to any Pi │
  ├───────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ wifi-watchdog.service │ Generic — systemd unit, same on any Pi │
  ├───────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ wifi-restored.sh      │ Device-specific — customize per Pi     │
  └───────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────┘

  To deploy on a new Pi:
  sudo cp wifi-watchdog.sh wifi-restored.sh /usr/local/bin/
  sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/wifi-watchdog.sh /usr/local/bin/wifi-restored.sh
  sudo cp wifi-watchdog.service /etc/systemd/system/
  sudo systemctl daemon-reload && sudo systemctl enable --now wifi-watchdog

  Then edit /usr/local/bin/wifi-restored.sh for whatever that Pi needs to do on reconnect.

